commit.message:
Feature #1563: Report SERVICE_STOPPED with an error code if SvcRun() raises an Exception. (#1566)

If SvcRun() raises an Exception then the final call to SetServiceStatus will be with a SERVICE_STATUS structure,
with dwCurrentState=SERVICE_STOPPED, dwWin32ExitCode=ERROR_SERVICE_SPECIFIC_ERROR and dwServiceSpecificExitCode non-zero.

This is so Services that have the "Enable Actions For Stops With Errors" / `failureflag` option enabled,
will have their recovery actions run when SvcRun() raises an Exception.

commit.message:
Do not jump past PY_INTERFACE_PRE/POSTCALLs (#1567)

The PY_INTERFACE_PRECALL macro defines a variable of type PyThreadState.
Jumping across it is an error in gcc/mingw.
